{"name": "storify", "metadata": {"name": "storify", "version": "0.0.5", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/benbaptist/storify", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["msgpack"], "summary": "A lightweight database system for Python", "upload_time": 1732133593}, "documentation": ["# Storify\n\nStorify is a dead-simple, lightweight Python database library that uses msgpack for efficient data serialization. \n\nIt provides a framework for data storage and retrieval, with an optional ORM model for interaction with data. \n\nStorify supports automatic backups and error handling, ensuring data integrity and reliability. \n\n## Features\n\n- Create and manage multiple msgpack-based databases with ease.\n- Lightweight ORM-esque model for easy interaction with data.\n- Automatic backups and data flushing to prevent data loss.\n- Built-in error handling to automatically recover from database corruption and loading issues.\n- Configurable save intervals for optimized performance.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install storify\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nHere's a simplified example of how to use the `storify` package:\n\n```python\nfrom storify import Storify\n\n# Initialize Storify\nstorify = Storify(root=\"example_data\")\ndb_name = \"example_db\"\n\n# Check if the database exists\nif storify.db_exists(db_name):\n    print(f\"Database '{db_name}' exists. It will be loaded.\")\n\n# Initialize a new database\n db = storify.get_db(name=db_name)\n\n# Add some data to the database \ndb[\"key1\"] = \"value1\" \ndb[\"key2\"] = \"value2\"\n\n# Get some data from the database\nprint(f\"key1: {db['key1']}\")\nprint(f\"key2: {db['key2']}\")\n\n# Flush all databases (force save)\nstorify.flush()\n```\n\nFor more complete examples, including how to use the ORM, please check the `examples` folder.\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "storify.dummylogger", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "storify.dummylogger.DummyLogger", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "storify.dummylogger.DummyLogger.info", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "msg", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "storify.dummylogger.DummyLogger.debug", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "msg", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "storify.dummylogger.DummyLogger.error", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "msg", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "storify.dummylogger.DummyLogger.warning", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "msg", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "storify.dummylogger.DummyLogger.traceback", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "msg", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "storify.database.backups", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "storify.database.backups.Backups", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "storify.database.backups.Backups.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "db", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "storify.database.backups.Backups.backup", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a backup of the database."]}, {"name": "storify.database.backups.Backups.db_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["def restore(self, backup_id):", "path = self.get_path_of_backup(backup_id)"]}, {"name": "storify.database.backups.Backups.backup_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "storify.database.backups.Backups.list", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["List all backups of the database."]}, {"name": "storify.database.backups.Backups.latest", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "storify.database.backups.Backups.last", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Get the oldest backup of the database."]}, {"name": "storify.database.backups.Backups.get_path_of_backup", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "backup_id", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "storify.model", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "storify.model.Model", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "storify.model.Model._key", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "storify.model.Model._keyname", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null,