        it defaults to the standard path based on the database name.\n\nRaises:\n    DatabaseLoadError: If the database cannot be loaded from the main file or any backups.\n\nThis method attempts to load the database from the specified file. If the main file\nis corrupted, it tries to load from available backups. If all attempts fail, it raises\na DatabaseLoadError."]}, {"name": "storify.database.Database.encode_type", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "storify.database.Database.decode_type", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "storify.database.Database.unpack", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "raw", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "storify.database.Database.flush", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Flush the database to disk."]}, {"name": "storify.database.Database.close", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Close the database. This will flush the database to disk and set the database as defunct."]}, {"name": "storify.database.Database.destroy", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Destroy the database. This will delete the database file from disk, but it will not remove backups."]}, {"name": "storify.database.Database.append", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwa